# =============================================================================
#  NCI вЂ” Trade Network Application  (COUNTRY Г— COUNTRY)
#  World Input-Output Database (WIOD), 2016 Release
#  Current prices, millions of USD
#
#  Riso & Zoia (2026) вЂ” Empirical Application: International Trade Networks
#
#  Logica:
#   Nodes  = countries (44 + ROW = 45)
#   Edges  = intermediate flows aggregated over all sectors
#             ГЈ[c,d] = (a[c,d] + a[d,c]) / 2   (average bidirectional coefficient)
#             A[c,d] = 1  if  ГЈ[c,d] > theta    (SYMMETRIC matrix)
#   Weights = w_c = VA_c / sum(VA)   (world value-added share by country)
#   Indices = Baseline NCI  vs  HHI  vs  Gini
#
#  Economic interpretation:
#   HHI  в†’ concentration of world VA (how large each country is)
#   NCI  в†’ are the largest countries also the most interconnected?
#           NCI >> HHI  вџ№  trade hubs coincide with the dominant countries
#
#  Note on symmetrization:
#   ГЈ[c,d] = (a[c,d] + a[d,c]) / 2  captures the AVERAGE intensity of the
#   bidirectional trade between c and d. An edge exists if both
#   directions are on average relevant. This is more conservative than
#   the OR (union) rule and more informative than AND (intersection).
# =============================================================================

